               <head>Grant; Higham; 1313</head>
               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111663">Higham (Higham etc)</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1313">1313</origDate>.
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Bole</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111663">Higham (Heyham)</placeName>
                        </persName> to <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Fyzs</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Fyzs">
                           <forename>Sara</forename> his wife</persName>, for a sum of money, of two half-acres of arable land, in the field of Heyham, one half-acre lying between the lands of <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Wayssepail</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName>
                           <forename>Humfrey</forename> of <surname>Palegrue</surname>
                        </persName>, and abutting on the lands of <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> of <surname>Passelewe</surname>
                        </persName>, and <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> 
                           <surname>Aleyn</surname>
                        </persName>, the other half-acre lying between the lands of <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Wayssepail</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Wayssepail</surname>, jun.</persName>, and abutting on the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Humfrey</forename> of <surname>Palegraue</surname>
                        </persName>, and on 'le fyldeweye'. 
                        Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_111663">Higham (Heyham)</placeName>, Sunday [16 Dec.] next after the feast of St Lucy, Virgin, 7 Ed. II [1313].
                     Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename>, <surname type="patronymic">son of Thomas</surname>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> 
                           <surname>Robbe</surname>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Passelewe</surname>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> of <surname>Saham</surname>
                        </persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> la <surname>Kersonere</surname> of Gaysle</persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> (<surname>Smith</surname>) '<surname>Fabro</surname>'</persName> of the same, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> '<surname>Clerico</surname>'</persName>(?) of the same, and others.
                     The seal is wanting.
                     Endorsed: De Joh'ne Bole.
                     </p>
